Meetup has made the following changes that affect the functioning of our virtual self-study group initiative:

Message Boards have been removed.

Event Comments are now the dedicated feature for organizers to communicate with members attending a specific event.

This virtual self-study group Meetup is a pilot test of these changes. If you have an interest in the topic of Project Management, please sign up and help us sort through these Meetup communication changes.

Introduction to Project Management

Are you an individual contributor looking to advance your career by moving into a manager role? Then, begin here and start learning the skills needed to manage projects and teams effectively.

LinkedIn has made the following course available for FREE for a limited time: LinkedIn Learning Highlights: Project Management. All you need to begin is a LinkedIn account. Participating will take less than an hour, and you will receive a Certificate of Completion to add to your LinkedIn profile.

A requirement for participating in this pilot:

Once you sign up you will use the Event Comments to update your progress and offer feedback.

NOTE #1: This virtual self-study group activity begins August 1, 2024 and ends August 31, 2024. (Meetup is not set up to handle multi-day events.)

Note #2: There is NO classroom instruction. There are NO Zoom meetings. There are NO scheduled appointments of any kind. You simply proceed at a pace that best fits into your current work/life schedule.

Invite your co-workers and fellow techies to join in the fun. Then, let's start managing!

Gene Babon

Co-Organizer & Chief Percolator
Boston PHP Meetup & Web Apprentices
